description.plain: Helene Immel, also known as Lenachka, is a singer/songwriter based in Los Angeles and Nashville. Immel is a German-born descendant of Russian immigrants, and was given the Russian nickname “Lenachka' as a child by her mother. In 2012, Lenachka moved to Los Angeles to pursue music full-time, and was subsequently discovered by producer Charlie Peacock after posting a cover of The Civil Wars and Taylor Swift’s "Safe & Sound” to YouTube. In 2014, Lenachka released her debut self-titled EP.

description.plain:
“I Want to Love You” is the first official single by Los Angeles based singer/songwriter Lenachka, as well as the first promotional single of her debut self-titled EP.

The track was produced by Charlie Peacock, [who discovered Lenachka in 2012.

An early version of the track was uploaded to Lenachka’s official YouTube channel on February 4, 2013.

The track was eventually released with updated production on September 23, 2014.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ToZD3qWcwZU
